Entrances to the building are located on both Fourth and Fifth Avenues between James and Cherry streets. . City Hall is open from 7 a.m. - 6 p.m., Monday through Friday.

name: Social Security Administration Office
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Two single-occupant gender neutral, accessible bathrooms in SSA waiting room on 9th floor. . Building had security on ground floor that requires you to remove coats, belts, bags etc and go through x-ray machine. No identity documents checked or anything.

name: Town Hall Seattle
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Great Hall lobby. Might only be open during paid events

name: Starbucks
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Need to be a customer. The employees unlock it for you.

name: 5th Avenue Theater
description: Gender-neutral restroom. On the right as soon. As you enter the theater.. All gender bathroom with individual stalls.

name: Starbucks
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Ask a barista for the door code.

name: Slate Coffee Roasters
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Straight in the back. . I figure you have to be a paying customer, but their coffee is fantastic. They take coffee to an art form.

name: Spooked in Seattle
description: Gender-neutral restroom. There are two single restrooms that are gender neutral. Sometimes there are gender signs up to reduce confusion with the tourists who would otherwise try relieving themselves in a closet, but no one cares which restroom is used and often they are used interchangeably.. They will ask you to be a paying customer unless you briefly explain your situation (to keep out the vagrant pioneer square population), but they are very lbgtqia+ friendly. If you would like to give back,

name: Starbucks
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Need a code from barista.

name: Cherry Street Coffee House
description: Gender-neutral restroom. In the far back down a hall past the counter and tables. . You have to be a paying customer, ask for the code.

name: Trabant Coffee & Chai / Pioneer Square
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Second  & James, between Seattle Flowers and Howard House Gallery. On the block north of Smith Tower.. Weekdays 6am -> 6pmWeekends 10am -> 5pmAwesome coffee!

name: Bill Speidel's Underground Tours
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Downstairs in the hallway by the introduction room, single stall "all gender" restrooms. Bar and Gift Shop gendered, but safe spaces.. The neighborhood has a large transient population, so if you don't have a ticket to the tour, browse the gift shop to use the restrooms there. Likely not to let you downstairs to introduction room bathrooms without a ticket.

name: Basement/Chinook Building
description: Gender-neutral restroom. This is in the basement. You need to use the elevator near the ATM on the first floor. I think there's signage.

name: Motif Seattle
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Main lobby, down the hallway next to the desks (not the elevators) to the left

name: Fat Shack
description: Public restroom. In the back past the back room, two single stall restrooms

name: City Centre
description:
Public restroom. Third floor behind Palomino restaurant.

. Buy a cake pop or croissant from Starbucks or cookie from Mrs. Fields on the first floor by the elevators and they'll give you the code if you ask. There may be separate codes for the different gender bathrooms, so make sure they give you the right one.

name: Act Theatre
description: Gender-neutral restroom. 2nd floor multistall gender neutral restrooms. I go for the plays, they are really fun to see, the actors are really professional.

name: Starbucks
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Two gender neutral restrooms. Both single stall.

name: Nightjar
description: Gender-neutral restroom. In the back, past the exit sign. A queer friendly nightclub with a cover most nights. Mention the app to gain access without paying.

name: 629 Pike St, Seattle, WA 98101, USA
description: Public restroom. 4th floor. Follow signs past the Richmond and Shilshole meeting rooms. . Meeting rooms of a hotel. Move like you belong and no one stops you.

name: Starbucks on the Pier
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Free to use for anyone

name: Emerson Salon
description: Gender-neutral restroom. In the back of salon. Kind of accessible but a tight fit around hair stations. . It is a hair salon. All of the stylists are queer/trans friendly, at least one is trans.

name: Chipotle
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Mon-Sun 11am-8pm. Found on yelp reviews: \"There is only one unisex bathroom which was pretty clean and well stocked.\"http://www.yelp.com/biz/chipotle-seattle-3#hrid:vu4SrtoxLh85mGS7JCyqZQ

name: Panama Hotel cafe
description: Gender-neutral restroom. one non-gendered bathroom downstairs, single occupancy, locking, not accessible

name: Washington State Convention Center
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Two small restrooms on the 4th floor and one large restroom (two formerly gendered restrooms combined) on the 6th floor.. Available to convention attendees (Ive used them for Sakura-con for the past three years). Unsure about the availability for the general public.

name: Seattle Convention Center
description: Gender-neutral restroom. On the second floor, it'll have a sign. You have to be a convention attendee

name: Starbucks
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Straight to the back on the left of interior, you can't miss it. . You do NOT have to buy anything - just ask a barista for the access code.

name: Regal Meridian 16
description: Public restroom. First floor, under "ADA Restrooms" sign in lobby. There are two single-occupancy restrooms marked gender neutral

name: Seattle Coffee Works
description: Gender-neutral restroom. You need a key :)

name: The Hub
description: Public restroom. First floor behind kitchen

name: Game works
description: Gender-neutral restroom. In restaurant area lower level.

name: Old Navy
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Ground floor in the back, to the right of the checkout counter

name: Great State Burger
description: Public restroom. In between the burger place and the ramen place. . Theres a code needed to use the restroom.

name: Caf Nordo Knife Room
description: Gender-neutral restroom. This is in the downstairs Knife Room space.

name: Nordstrom
description: Public restroom. On the third or fourth floor, right next to the Sky Bridge that connects to the mall. There is a small kiosk like thing that sell candy and knick knacks to the left of it. . Just look around a little, the person running the kiosk will probably wave.

name: Cafe Yum
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Next to kitchen, down hall to right of counter . Must be paying customer

name: Pacific Place
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Top floor. Take escalators up, to right of the theater entrance.. Marked as family restroom. You have to call a number and have security let you in. If you do not have a child with you, they may question you. Sometimes they wait outside the restroom and check if as soon as you step out.

name: Victrola
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Up the stairs or lift behind the Victrola or lobby in the Macys building.

name: Seattle Aquarium
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Hidden by the otters, outside! there are gendered bathrooms inside, but gender neutral ones just past the otter tanks outside. . You have to pay to get into the aquarium, so this is really just useful for folks that were going to visit the aquarium and were worried about bathrooms there

name: Third Culture Coffee x Callus
description: Gender-neutral restroom. In the back, there are signs to follow to the restroom. Must be paying customer, a passcode will be given on receipt; there are two restrooms

name: Pike Market Food Bank
description: Gender-neutral restroom. If you are in the market, go to the sky bridge and hit P5 to go to the food bank.

name: Bacco Cafe/ Chan Seattle
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Have to be a paying customer

name: King Street Station
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Near the seating area. Family restroom; next to the men's restroom

name: 1600 Post Alley, Seattle, WA 98101, USA
description: Gender-neutral restroom. In the back past the kitchen. Probably need to be a paying customer

name: hoot/heard/cassette
description: Gender-neutral restroom. enter through hoot for wheel chair accessibility!. safe for all people, staff will fight transphobes

name: Local Color
description: Gender-neutral restroom. On the main road in Pike Place market, cross street Pine.. Coffee shop with art for sale.www.localcolorseattle.comFree wifi.

name: Paramount Theatre
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Down a hallway near the back of the main floor.. You probably have to be attending a show/a customer.

name: Seattle Aquarium
description: Gender-neutral restroom. There are two single stall bathrooms in the second building upstairs by the otters that are single stall and marked "all genders".. You have to have an admission ticket to use these, but if you happen to be at the aquarium this could be helpful.

name: General Porpoise
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Paying customers

name: Seattle Westin
description: Public restroom. Enter off of Westlake Ave through the valet area. When facing the escalators turn left down a hallway next to the south tower elevators. First door on the right. . Note: the hallway may not always be open. This is not near the lobby but in the conference area

name: Seattle Aquarium
description: Public restroom. By the marine animals exhibit. Two single stalls available.

name: Vietlicious
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Across from the entrance.. Code is 4152. Two unisex bathrooms. Don't know whether you have to order something or not.

name: Urara
description: Gender-neutral restroom

name: Hard Rock Cafe
description: Public restroom. Single stall unisex

name: Tribeca
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Restaurant

name: Unicorn Crepes
description: Gender-neutral restroom. By the ordering counter. Solitary unisex bathroom which requires a key, designated customers-only. . Not only is it gender-neutral, it is one of the most fabulous bathrooms in Seattle. Words really can't describe it. I'm not sure it's entirely accessible, however. Although it is customers-only, it's well worth it to stop by and try these fabulous Japanese crepes... and get a free milk tea from an automated machine.

name: Jupiter Bar
description: Public restroom. Back of bar by arcade. You have to be 21+ with ID, but you don't have to buy anything. Restroom in in back of bar by arcade section

name: Roccos Pizza
description: Gender-neutral restroom. At the very back.. You have to be a paying customer but they have pizza by the slice to go. There are two of them.

name: Starbucks Reserve Roastery and Tasting Room
description: Gender-neutral restroom

name: Victrola Coffee Inc
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Located between Bellevue Ave & Minor Ave.. Mon-Fri 6:30 am - 8 pmSat-Sun 7:30 am - 8 pm

name: Bok a Bok Fried Chicken
description: Public restroom. Enter and then turn left. You'll see a sign to go down the hall.. No keys needed.

name: Seatown Seabar
description: Gender-neutral restroom

name: Serious Pie
description: Gender-neutral restroom. You should be a customer but you can probably sneak in at peak hours. We did!

name: First Covenant Church
description: Gender-neutral restroom. On the first floor of the church, when the church is open, there is a single unisex stall on the righthand side of the sanctuary, just above some stairs that lead down to the church basement.. Enjoy the artwork outside the church on Pike, and check out some of the historical photos inside while you're there.

name: Oasis bubble tea
description: Public restroom. Key needed

name: Gay City Health Project
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Up ramp in Gay City Auditorium (large room directly across from entrance)

name: Juliano's
description: Gender-neutral restroom. All the way in the back of the resturaunt.. This place has the advantage of weird hours (open to 1:30 am or 3:00 am depending on the day), but due to it's size it's impossible to slip in and out unnoticed just to use the bathroom... Not that you'd want to though, once you smelled the pizza.

name: Center for LGBT Health/Kaladi Bros. coffee
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Queerly gendered restroom. Two single stall locking restrooms labeled Kenneth and Barb, both drag queen barbie dolls. It is safe to use either restroom

name: goPok
description: Public restroom. Large locked single stall restroom. In the back corner diagonal from the door, past the counter.. For paying customers, typically busy.

name: Kaladi Brothers
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Key is at the front, bathrooms are to the right of the ordering area toward the back.. Fun chalk board walls. Nice people. Great company.

name: SweetGrass Food Co
description: Gender-neutral restroom

description: Gender-neutral restroom. Right hand side to the back. Preferably for paying customers, but if you ask nicely staff will let anyone use restrooms

name: Sun Liquor
description: Gender-neutral restroom

name: World Pizza
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Go straight in past the booths to the end of the hall.. Also a safe place. Chill folks who will let you use the bathroom without paying for something.

name: The Table
description: Gender-neutral restroom. All the way in the back on the left

name: Bauhaus
description: Public restroom. Back behind the kitchen area. bauhaus has two single stall locking bathrooms, one that has an M and one that has a W but it is very strongly the culture of the regulars to use whatever bathroom is first available/treat them as gender neutral bathrooms, regardless of whatever bathroom people typically use or where they sit on the genderqueer spectrum.just walk right in. you don't have to buy anything. bauhaus employees are some of the nicest people on earth. i go there every

name: Potbelly Sandwich Shop
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Open to public, no key or access code needed

name: Eastern Cafe
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Second floor, in the back.. Technically paying customers only but you don't need a key.

name: Seattle Counseling Services
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Get out the elevator take a left, then take a left  and go down the hallway and then take the first left you see.

name: Potbelly Sandwich Shop
description: Gender-neutral restroom. At the side door entrance. Supposed to be a paying customer but if you ask when it's not busy they usually let you. Need a key.

name: Romio's Pizza and Pasta
description: Gender-neutral restroom

name: Dilettante Mocha Cafe
description: Gender-neutral restroom. Visible from front door . customers only. Really yummy coffee.

address: MLK Junior Way between 11th and Earnest S Brazill street

name: 1702 Pacific Ave, Tacoma, WA 98402, USA

address: 1717 S J St, Tacoma, WA  98405, United States

name: W.W. Seymour Botanical Conservatory
description: Gender-neutral restroom. From the entrance take the right hand path all the way back.. Suggested donation but not monitored

description: Gender-neutral restroom. First floor. You must be a YWCA client or staff member to use.  Community members can also request tours and can use the bathrooms.

name: King's Books

When I lived in the area, they had a visibly gender-variant employee, and are very liberal, so if you were to tell them your reason for going there, I do not think they would require you to shop.

If anyone bothers you, go into the undergraduate lounge (big green room) and tell someone if you need help, or just sit on a couch and wait it out.

name: University of Washington Tacoma
description: Public restroom. Located in Many University buildings . Located in Many University buildings

name: The Village Perk

name: Alfred's cafe

name: Wok &Teriyaki

name: Target

Blow it up to your heart's delight.Large private bathroom with high powered jet flush toilet and usually stocked with an ample supply of air freshener makes for an especially pleasing pooping experience.  There is also an air powered hand dryer for your amusement. Enjoy!

The building is open until 6:00 pm for public access, and after 6:00 pm to students in the sciences. The fourth floor has a completely neutral bathroom, as well as a neutral shower.

name: Blue Mouse theater

name: Five Guys

They are quite large, separate room/single stall, locking unisex bathrooms.

name: Neato Burrito/Baby Bar

name: ifly
description:
Public restroom. The bathroom on the ground floor is down the hallway between the front desk and the stairs, on the left side. The second-floor bathroom is up the stairs, and down the hallway to your left when facing the indoor-skydiving wind-tunnel. . The ground floor has two accessible, gendered single stalls. 
The second floor has a gender-neutral, accessible single-stall.
